cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel type of image search and presents a framework for interactive top-k geo-tagged image query. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with multimedia data with geographical information. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper proposes a new index structure (GIR-Tree) for efficient searching in a large-scale database. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper considers similarity of visual content in the image search. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithm (GI-SUPER Search) based on a new notion called superior relationship.
